Public Art Map Portland

Winston Saunders

March 15, 2016

SUMMARY:

The locations of public art in Portland, Oregon, are avail on the Civic Apps. Sadly, the data do not appear to be updated regularly. Nevertheless this could be a valuable public resource.

To get the data use the following function. The data are read direcntly from my github repo.

## Loading required package: bitops

The variables for the function are defined as below. The train.column.types simplifies the data cleaning for analysis.

        file.path <- "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ww44ss/public_art/master/"

Now we can get the data quickly

## Warning: Removed 20 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

A more detailed zoom of downtown. Note that points are plotted with an alpha of 0.5 to show where multiple artwork are located.
